summary:
European qualified lawyer with 14+ years’ experience working as in-house legal counsel at international companies with a focus on commercial contracts, data protection, and brand marketing strategies in a technology-driven environment, balancing innovative and commercial mindsets while ensuring legal compliance.

Broad-based career path working for French, American, Dutch, Japanese, and Brazilian organizations from different industries, including Information Technology & Services, Automotive, Sports, Higher Education, and Software Development.

𝐂𝐚𝐫𝐞𝐞𝐫 𝐡𝐢𝐠𝐡𝐥𝐢𝐠𝐡𝐭𝐬:

- Responsible for providing legal advice on a variety of commercial strategies (B2B/B2C) at companies from different industries in LATAM and EMEA;
- Responsible for providing legal advice on data protection and privacy on a global level;
- Responsible for drafting, reviewing, and negotiating strategic sponsorship / endorsement agreements to promote brand marketing strategies across LATAM and EMEA; 
- Played a key role in the implementation of the e-commerce platform at Michelin South America;
- Played a key role in the implementation of the hybrid education model at Leiden University;

𝐄𝐝𝐮𝐜𝐚𝐭𝐢𝐨𝐧 𝐡𝐢𝐠𝐡𝐥𝐢𝐠𝐡𝐭𝐬:

- Hold an Advanced LL.M. in Law and Digital Technologies from Leiden University;
- Hold a professional data protection officer certification from Maastricht University (ECPC-B DPO);
- Certified Information Privacy Professional/Europe (CIPP/E);
- Admitted to practice law in Brazil and Portugal;

𝗔𝘄𝗮𝗿𝗱𝘀:

- Michelin Professional of the Year 2016;
- Michelin Professional of the Year 2017;

𝐀𝐫𝐞𝐚𝐬 𝐨𝐟 𝐞𝐱𝐩𝐞𝐫𝐢𝐞𝐧𝐜𝐞:

• Contracts: Commercial (B2B/B2C); ICT/SaaS, and Procurement;
• Digital, Business, and Consumer Law;
• Sponsorship / Endorsement Agreements;
• E-commerce / Internet / Advertising Law;
• Data Protection / Privacy (GDPR/LGPD);
• Compliance & Corporate Governance;
• M&A / Due Diligences; 
• Competition Law;

