Reporting directly to the Head of Legal, I am a Lead Counsel for Tire Solutions and Subscription Solutions in EMIA.

Main activities:

• Provide a variety of general commercial legal guidance to Bridgestone's business lines (Tire Solutions, Data Solutions, and Subscription Solutions) ensuring that their activities, projects, and business practices are in compliance with internal policies and external regulation;
• Responsible for drafting, reviewing, and negotiating different types of commercial contracts, including dealership agreements for all Bridgestone Mobility Solutions dealers in EMIA;
• Play a key role in digital strategies providing practical legal advice to business partners across Sales, Product, IT, and Marketing;
• Provide legal advice on data protection standards, including protection of personal data from employees, consumers, and commercial partners;
• Working closely with the DPO on digital strategies and data protection impact assessments (DPIA);
• Give training sessions on compliance topics to staff members across different business units;

Reporting directly to the General Counsel, I was responsible for Commercial & Privacy in EMEA.

Main 𝗣𝗿𝗶𝘃𝗮𝗰𝘆 activities:

• As Shimano’s Data Protection Officer (DPO) and Privacy Lead, act as the primary point of contact within the organization for members of staff, data subjects, regulators, and any relevant public bodies on issues related to data protection;
• Provide legal advice on data protection standards, including protection of personal data from employees, consumers, and commercial partners;
• Conduct data protection impact assessments (DPIAs) to help business assess and mitigate risks related to processing personal data;
• Give training sessions on data protection to staff members across different business units who are involved in data handling;
• Ensure company’s strategies and practices are in accordance with privacy laws;

Main 𝗖𝗼𝗺𝗺𝗲𝗿𝗰𝗶𝗮𝗹 activities:

• Provide a variety of general commercial legal guidance to all Shimano's business lines (bike, fishing, and rowing ) ensuring that their activities, projects, and business practices are in compliance with internal norms and external regulation;
• Play a key role in e-commerce and digital strategies providing practical legal advice to business partners across Sales, Product, IT, and Marketing;
• Responsible for drafting, reviewing, and negotiating different types of commercial contracts, including B2B agreements with bike manufacturers and contracts with a focus on B2C strategies, such as distributorship agreements and dealership agreements for all Shimano Service Centers in EMEA;
• Responsible for drafting, reviewing, and negotiating strategic partnerships agreements to promote Shimano’s brand;

Reporting directly to the Program Director, Academic Coordinator, and Program Coordinator, I was responsible for the following tasks:

• Project member of the hybrid education model (online + on-campus lectures) of the Advanced LL.M. in Law and Digital Technologies;
• Member of the Center for Law and Digital Technologies (eLaw), which has a leading role in research and education on law and digital technologies (regulation, privacy, data protection, etc);
• Supporting professors in the preparation and implementation of the hybrid education model;
• Acting as a facilitator for both on-campus and online classes;

